headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 45 points and 16 rebounds, Dakota Mathias’ only basket of the game was a go-ahead 3-pointer with 26.1 seconds left and the Philadelphia 76ers hung on to beat the undermanned Miami Heat 137-134 in overtime on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 45, Mathias wins it for 76ers in OT on 3

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant had 34 points, 13 assists and nine rebounds, Bruce Brown made a huge contribution while starting for the absent Kyrie Irving, and the Brooklyn Nets rallied from 18 down to beat the Denver Nuggets 122-116 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 34, Nets charge back from 18 down, top Nuggets

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 27 points and the Utah Jazz rolled to a 117-87 win over the injury-depleted Cleveland Cavaliers, wrapping up their six-game road trip Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz end shortened trip with 117-87 win over depleted Cavs

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 26 points in just more than three quarters and the Los Angeles Lakers never trailed in a 117-100 rout of the Houston Rockets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 26 as Lakers roll over Rockets 117-100

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Lonnie Walker IV scored 24 points and San Antonio beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 112-102 on Tuesday night, allowing the Spurs to finish a five-game trip with four wins.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs finish strong road trip with 112-102 win over Thunder

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Myles Turner hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with 2:59 to play and scored 22 points, Aaron Holiday converted a layup on the next possession and the Indiana Pacers stymied Stephen Curry and the Golden State Warriors 104-95 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers stymie Curry, bounce back to beat Warriors 104-95
